<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFD2FFF9FF6BFC25FBD9FB0A" pageId="8" pageNumber="283" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFD2FFF9FF6BFC25FBD9FB0A" blockId="8.[151,1127,963,1242]" pageId="8" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD2FFF9FF6BFC25FEB8FC6A" bold="true" box="[151,262,963,986]" pageId="8" pageNumber="283">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFD2FFF9FEF0FC25FE1CFC6A" author="BUZZI" box="[268,418,963,986]" firstAuthor="BUZZI" pageId="8" pageNumber="283" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref48871" refString="BUZZI J. Z. 1996 a: A new species of Agroiconota Spaeth from Brazil (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae). Coleopterists Bulletin 50: 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1996" yearSuffix="a">BUZZI (1996a)</bibRefCitation>
described this species from a single specimen, provided a detailed description and figure of dorsal habitus, enabling identification of this taxon. 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFD2FFF9FC54FC05FBD9FC4A" author="BOROWIEC" box="[936,1127,995,1018]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="8" pageNumber="283" pagination="387 - 393" refId="ref48243" refString="BOROWIEC L. 1998 b: Agroiconota judaica (Fabricius, 1781) and A. inedita (Boheman, 1855) - distinct species (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae). Genus 9: 387 - 393." type="journal article" year="1998" yearSuffix="b">BOROWIEC (1998b)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized it with 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD2FFF9FE86FBE5FDBCFBAA" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[378,514,1027,1050]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Agroiconota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subvittata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD2FFF9FE86FBE5FDBCFBAA" box="[378,514,1027,1050]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="283">A. subvittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on similar colour pattern formed by red stripes on yellow elytra. However, the 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFD2FFF9FE42FBC5FDA5FB8A" box="[446,539,1059,1082]" pageId="8" pageNumber="283">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD2FFF9FDC7FBC5FD7EFB8A" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[571,704,1059,1082]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Agroiconota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subvittata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD2FFF9FDC7FBC5FD7EFB8A" box="[571,704,1059,1082]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="283">A. subvittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the red stripes irregular due to punctures with large black areolae, particularly in the first and second stripe, while 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD2FFF9FC12FBA5FBD9FBEA" authorityName="Buzzi" authorityYear="1996" box="[1006,1127,1091,1114]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Agroiconota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="urbanae">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD2FFF9FC12FBA5FBD9FBEA" box="[1006,1127,1091,1114]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="283">A. urbanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has these regular and bordered with small black punctures (see Figs 15 and 
<quantity id="282ED3D3FFD2FFF9FC3CFB85FC49FBCA" box="[960,1015,1123,1146]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.398" pageId="8" pageNumber="283" unit="in" value="37.0">37 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFD2FFF9FC02FB85FF6EFB2A" author="BOROWIEC" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" journalOrPublisher="Annales Zoologici (Warszawa)" pageId="8" pageNumber="283" pagination="61 - 74" part="55" refId="ref48410" refString="BOROWIEC L. 2005: Six new species of the genus Agroiconota Spaeth, 1913 (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae), with a key to the genus. Annales Zoologici (Warszawa) 55: 61 - 74." title="Six new species of the genus Agroiconota Spaeth, 1913 (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae), with a key to the genus" type="journal article" year="2005">BOROWIEC 2005</bibRefCitation>
). Therefore I restore the species status of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD2FFF9FD86FB65FD53FB2A" authorityName="Buzzi" authorityYear="1996" box="[634,749,1155,1178]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Agroiconota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="urbanae">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD2FFF9FD86FB65FD53FB2A" box="[634,749,1155,1178]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="283">A. urbanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD2FFF9FC56FB65FB90FB2A" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[938,1070,1155,1178]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Agroiconota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subvittata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD2FFF9FC56FB65FB90FB2A" box="[938,1070,1155,1178]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="283">A. subvittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Corumbá published by 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFD2FFF9FE73FB45FDFBFB0A" author="BOROWIEC" box="[399,581,1187,1210]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="8" pageNumber="283" pagination="119 - 251" refId="ref48151" refString="BOROWIEC L. 1996: Faunistic records of Neotropical Cassidinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Polskie Pismo Entomologiczne 65: 119 - 251." type="journal article" year="1996">BOROWIEC (1996)</bibRefCitation>
belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD2FFF9FD42FB45FC8AFB0A" authorityName="Buzzi" authorityYear="1996" box="[702,820,1187,1210]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Agroiconota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="urbanae">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD2FFF9FD42FB45FC8AFB0A" box="[702,820,1187,1210]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="283">A. urbanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L. Borowiec, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
